    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise <br></p>
<p>The formula for the volume of a cylinder is \(V = \pi r^2h \).
Find \(V\) when \(r = {@ru1@}\), \(h = {@hu1@}\).&nbsp;<span style="font-size: calc(0.90375rem + 0.045vw);">Round your answer to 3 significant figures and include the appropriate units.</span></p>
<br>
<p>\(V =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We have \(r = {@ru1@}\) and \(h = {@hu1@}\). Substituting these values into the formula we find:\[\begin{aligned} V &amp;=\pi r^2h\\ &amp;= \pi \cdot ({@ru1@})^2 \cdot {@hu1@}\\ &amp;= \pi \cdot {@ru1^2@} \cdot {@hu1@}\\ &amp;= \pi \cdot {@ru1^2*hu1@}\\ &amp;= {@stackunits(float(%pi*(r1^2)*h1), cm^3)@}\\ &amp;= {@ta@} \text{ }_{\text{3.s.f}} \qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\end{aligned}\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
